from internet:
&quot;Austin Dam truly is an unusual sight - a broken monument to the power of nature and the folly of man. The fractured remains still stand, 77 years after the large concrete dam ruptured and wiped out the north-central Pennsylvania town of Austin on a sunny autumn afternoon. Within a couple of years, the dam, located along Route 872 in Potter County about a mile north of Austin, finally may become a park - a memorial to at least 78 people who died in the tragedy.&quot;
